474 REGISTRUM DE ABERBROTHOC.

The abbot lets for nineteen years to Robert Lessy and Cristiane Wardlau his wife, and to their heirs and affignees of no higher degree, the teind- sheaves of Innerpeffyr belonging to the said Robert in heritage and lying in the parish of Arbroyth and diocese of Sanctandros—paying yearly 4 bolls of wheat‚ 10 bolls of bear, and 18 bolls of meal, to be delivered at the granall of Arbroyth · 5 December 1527.

The abbot grants to Robert Lessy of Innerpeffyr for life a yearly penfion of 1510 ScotS, on condition that he shall appear as procurator for the abbot and convent in all causes against all persons, except those by whom he has been previoussy engaged, before the Lords of Council‚ Seffion, and Parliament, and give them his counsel in the same as often as required · 5 December 1527.
